               <msContents>
                  <summary>Book of Life, part of the Bandlet of Righteousness, ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡. Manuscript
                     in black and red ink. First page contains a decorative cross. Substantial
                     damage to some pages. A description of the object is given: "The little scroll
                     belongs to the common literature of Lefafa sedq (bandlet of truth), principally
                     used for burial with the deceased. That is, prayers of Mary, here the part
                     called the Mashafa heywat (book of life). It is represented by innumerable
                     copies in libraries and elsewhere." </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title type="complete" ref="LIT1758Lefafa">here called Book of Life (<foreign
                           xml:lang="gez">መጽሐፈ ሕይወት</foreign>)</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
